attributes.Long form description: The student is screwing the legs of a table into the shelves. They start with the middle shelf and then move to the top shelf. They screw in all four legs and then tighten the hex socket heads.

attributes.Transcription: Now we are looking at some Ikea furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inspects the shelf regularly.

attributes.Transcription: You should start by taking one of the shelves and put it standing on the table, laying on the longest side.
So put it up on the table and please turn it around so it's on the longest side.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The longest side should be on the table so it's more stable.

attributes.Transcription: So the longest side should be on the table so it's more stable.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should rotate it like ninety degrees left or right.

attributes.Transcription: So please just rotate it like ninety degrees left or right.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Ninety degrees should be in towards the direction.

attributes.Transcription: So now ninety degrees in, towards your direction.
And you can start assembling a first leg with this shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the first leg to the middle shelf of the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The instructor corrects him that he should start in the middle of the leg.

attributes.Transcription: This shelf will be the middle shelf so it should be aligned with the middle holes in the leg.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the second leg to the middle shelf of the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The instructor corrects him that he must rotate the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Please rotate the shelf so that one leg is laying on the table so it's holding in by itself.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the hex socket head.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the third leg to the middle shelf of the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should not screw the screws too much.

attributes.Transcription: You should not screw the screws too much because you are going to tighten them at end.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the fourth leg to the middle shelf of the table.
The student screws the first leg to the top shelf of the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The Instructor suggests leaving the furniture as it was.

attributes.Transcription: You should leave the shelf laying on the side and place the last shelf at the  top.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the hex socket head.

attributes.Action sentence: The student tightens all the hex socket heads.

attributes.Transcription: Now please put the shelf up again and tighten all the screws.
It's over. You can press the stop button.
